---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import config from '../data/config.json';

const { conference } = config;
---

<Layout title="Home">

<section class="hero-pic">
    <div class="hero-image"></div>
</section>

	<section class="hero">
        <div class="container hero-content">
            <h1>100 Years of Stafford Beer</h1>
            <p class="hero-subtitle">Celebrating his Life, his Legacy and Beyond</p>
            <p class="hero-date">{conference.dates}</p>
            <p class="hero-location">{conference.location}</p>
            <div class="hero-actions">
                <a href="/register" class="btn">Registration Information</a>
                <a href="/about" class="btn btn-secondary">About the Conference</a>
            </div>
        </div>
	</section>

    <section class="intro">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>A Global Centenary Celebration</h2>
            <p>In 2026, Metaphorum is inviting you to celebrate with us the centenary of the birth of Stafford Beer, one of the most influential figures in Cybernetics and Systems Thinking. More than fifty years after his invention of the Viable System Model and Team Syntegrity, Beer's work remains urgently relevant as organisations and societies confront escalating complexity, ecological limits, technological disruption, and crises of governance.
Metaphorum 2026 invites the global cyber-systemic community to reflect, reconnect, and reimagine organisational cybernetics through several interwoven themes. Through them we aim to honour Beer’s legacy while opening space for critical reflection and ways of continuing developing his theories and related practice.
</p>
            
            <div class="features-grid">
                <div class="feature highlight">
                    <h3>Conference Highlights</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Documentary Screening:</strong> ‘100 Years of Stafford Beer’</li>
                        <li><strong>Festschrift Book Launch:</strong> A 100 Years of Stafford Beer’: A cyber-systemic legacy, whose time has come’. Eds Angela Espinosa, Markus Schwaninger, Jose Perez-Rios</li>
                        <li><strong>Journal Launch:</strong> Metaphorum Journal ‘Organisational Systems’</li>
                        <li><strong>Academic Contributions:</strong> Panels, Presentations, Workshops, Poster Sessions</li>

                        <li><strong>Creative Contributions:</strong> Videos, exhibitions, music, poetry, and arts</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="feature venue-brief">
                    <h3>Hosted At</h3>
                    <p><strong>Alliance Manchester Business School (AMBS)</strong></p>
                    <p>In collaboration with the World Organization for Systems and Cybernetics (WOSC) and the Centre for Systems Studies (University of Hull).</p>
                    <a href="/venue">View Venue & Travel Info &rarr;</a>

<br>
                     <h3>In collaboration with:</h3>
                    
                    <p>
                    World Organisation of Systems and Cybernetics (WOSC) 
                    </p>
                    
                    <p>
                    Centre for Systems Studies, University of Hull (CSS)
                    </p>
                    
                    <p>
                    American Society of Cybernetics (ASC) 
                    </p>

                    <p>
                    International Federation for Systems Research (IFSR)
                    </p>
                    <p>
                    John Moores University - Stafford Beer Archive Collection
                    </p>

                 <p>
                The International Network for Democratic Economic Planning <a href="https://www.indep.network/about/">(INDEP)</a>
                </p> 

                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="publication-opportunities" style="margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h2>Publication Opportunities</h2>


                <div class="feature highlight" style="background: var(--color-background-alt); padding: 2rem; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-top: 4px solid var(--color-accent);">





<div class="feature highlight" style="background: var(--color-background-alt); padding: 2rem; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-top: 4px solid var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: 2rem;">
    <h3 style="margin-top: 0; color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 1rem;">Special Issue Invitation for Systems Research and Behavioural Science</h3>


<p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.6;">
    We are pleased to announce that selected high-quality papers presented at Metaphorum 2026 and associated events will be invited for consideration in the Special Issue: <strong>The End of the Beginning: Toward the Futures of CyberSystemics</strong>, published in <em>Systems Research and Behavioural Science</em> by Wiley.
</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.6;">
    The Special Issue welcomes original research, critical reviews, and conceptual papers engaging with the Viable System Model (VSM), Team Syntegrity, and related cybernetic frameworks. Contributions are invited from scholars, practitioners, and early-career researchers across systems sciences, organisational cybernetics, governance studies, and cognate fields.
</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6;">
    All manuscripts will be handled through the SRBS Wiley submission portal and subjected to the journal’s standard double-blind peer-review process. The Guest Editor team will conduct an initial screening for scope and quality.
</p>



<p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
    For further information on the full Call for Papers, submission guidelines, and themes,
    <a href="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/page/journal/10991743a/homepage/call-for-papers" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: bold; text-decoration: none;">
        Read More &rarr;
    </a>
</p>


</div>







                    









                    <h3 style="margin-top: 0; color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 1rem;">Special Issue Invitation for Systemic Practice & Action Research</h3>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.6;">
                        We are pleased to announce that selected high-quality papers presented at the Metaphorum Conference 2026 will be invited to be considered for the Special Issue: <strong>Toward Resilient, Just, and Ethical Viable Systems: Cybernetics, Resilience, and Socio-Ecological Futures</strong> of Systemic Practice and Action Research, published by Springer Nature.
                    </p>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.6;">
                        This special issue invites contributions that explore how the Viable System Model (VSM) and its cybernetic principles can strengthen societal and organisational responses to complexity by enhancing resilience, supporting regeneration, and enabling democratic and ethically grounded governance. It welcomes theoretical developments and practice-based insights that extend or reinterpret the VSM in light of contemporary socio-ecological challenges. We encourage contributions that critically engage with the VSM's architecture, integrate it with complementary methodologies, or present empirical cases that yield theoretical insights.
                    </p>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                        For Further information regarding Themes, Topics of interest, and submission guidelines, <a href="/publication" style="color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: bold; text-decoration: none;">Read More &rarr;</a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

             <div class="important-info">
                <h3>Key Dates</h3>
                <div class="dates-list">
                    <div class="date-item">
                        <span class="date-label">Registration Opens</span>
                        <span class="date-value">February 2026</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="date-item">
                        <span class="date-label">Conference</span>
                        <span class="date-value">Sept 17-19, 2026</span>
                    </div>

                   <div class="date-item">
                        <span class="date-label">DEADLINE FOR ABSTRACTS SUBMISSION</span>
                        <span class="date-value">July 17, 2026</span>
                    </div>

                     <div class="date-item">
                        <span class="date-label">Stafford's 100th Birthday</span>
                        <span class="date-value">Sept 25, 2026</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>

<style>
    .hero {
        background-color: var(--color-primary);
        color: white;
        padding: 2rem 0;
        text-align: center;
    }
.hero-pic {
    position: relative;
    height: 80vh; /* adjust as needed */
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    overflow: hidden;
    color: white;
}
.hero-image {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image: url('/mainPicture.png'); /* remove /public */
    background-size: contain;
    background-position: center;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-color: var(--color-primary); /* fills empty space */
    z-index: 0;
}

    .hero h1 {
        color: white;
        font-size: 3rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .hero-subtitle {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        font-style: italic;
        opacity: 0.9;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        font-family: var(--font-heading);
    }

    .hero-date, .hero-location {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .hero-actions {
        margin-top: 2rem;
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
        justify-content: center;
    }

    .lead {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        max-width: 900px;
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
        font-weight: 300;
        line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .features-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
        gap: 2rem;
        margin-top: 3rem;
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .feature {
        background: var(--color-background-alt);
        padding: 2rem;
        border-radius: 8px;
        border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }

    .feature h3 {
        margin-top: 0;
        color: var(--color-primary);
    }

    .highlight ul {
        list-style: none;
        padding: 0;
    }

    .highlight li {
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        padding-left: 1.25rem;
        position: relative;
    }

    .highlight li::before {
        content: "•";
        color: var(--color-accent);
        position: absolute;
        left: 0;
        font-weight: bold;
    }

    .important-info {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        padding-top: 3rem;
    }

    .dates-list {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 3rem;
    }

    .date-item {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
    }

    .date-label {
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.05em;
        color: var(--color-text-light);
    }

    .date-value {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--color-primary);
    }
</style>
